The Conn Smythe Trophy for the 2008 National Hockey League (NHL) playoffs was awarded to Henrik Zetterberg of the Detroit Red Wings. Zetterberg helped lead the Red Wings to the Stanley Cup championship with his outstanding play throughout the playoffs, recording 13 goals and 14 assists in 22 games. He was a key player in the Red Wings' championship run and was named the most valuable player of the playoffs by the Professional Hockey Writers' Association.